div.h2: Step-by-step tensor reshape: [batch, heads, seq, d_k] [batch, seq, d_model]

div.p: Memory layout: heads seq d_k contiguous
Operation: reshape(batch, seq, -1) or .view(batch, seq, num_heads * d_k)
After transpose, tensor may be non-contiguous. Call .contiguous() before .view() if needed.
*Transpose only changes stride metadata, not data layout
